red)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e138" source="Technical Approach to Safety" target="Factor 3 - Technical Approach"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.65</data><data key="d5">The instruction details a technical approach focused on safety, which semantically overlaps with the broader technical approach evaluation in Factor 3 covering methodology for performance objectives and risk mitigation. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e139" source="Instructions To Offerors Competitive Acquisition" target="Corporate Experience"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.55</data><data key="d5">General instructions to offerors in Section L guide the submission format and structure for corporate experience examples required under this evaluation factor. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e140" source="Instructions To Offerors Competitive Acquisition" target="Past Performance"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.55</data><data key="d5">Section L instructions modify proposal submission on an all-or-none basis, guiding how past performance information like CPARS and PPQs is provided for evaluation. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e141" source="Option Line Item 0003" target="Factor 2 - Management Approach"><data key="d3">GUIDES</data><data key="d4">0.4</data><data key="d5">The instruction on inspection and acceptance at destination relates to quality management systems evaluated in Factor 2's management approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e142" source="Quality Control Program" target="Management Approach"><data key="d3">EVALUATED_BY</data><data key="d4">0.8</data><data key="d5">The requirement for an effective quality control program matches the quality management system component evaluated in Factor 2 - Management Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e143" source="Transition Period" target="Management Approach"><data key="d3">EVALUATED_BY</data><data key="d4">0.75</data><data key="d5">The 90-day mobilization and demobilization periods relate to phase-in plans assessed under Factor 2 - Management Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e144" source="Small Business Participation" target="Small Business Utilization and Participation Factor"><data key="d3">EVALUATED_BY</data><data key="d4">0.9</data><data key="d5">Semantic overlap in requiring maximum small business opportunities and 20% value aligns with the factor's assessment of SBSP commitments. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e145" source="PM Requirements" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">EVALUATED_BY</data><data key="d4">0.7</data><data key="d5">Preventive maintenance tasks as part of performance methodology are evaluated through the technical methods for meeting objectives in Factor 3 - Technical Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e146" source="IMP Requirements" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">EVALUATED_BY</data><data key="d4">0.7</data><data key="d5">Inspection, maintenance, and preservation tasks share technical concepts with the methodology for performance objectives in Factor 3 - Technical Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e147" source="OEM Specifications" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">EVALUATED_BY</data><data key="d4">0.65</data><data key="d5">Maintaining systems per OEM guidelines relates to the systems approach and technical solutions evaluated in Factor 3 - Technical Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e148" source="Environmental" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">EVALUATED_BY</data><data key="d4">0.6</data><data key="d5">Environmental services and plans under Base Operations Support align with the technical methodology for performance objectives across annexes in Factor 3. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e149" source="Watchstanding Services" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">EVALUATED_BY</data><data key="d4">0.6</data><data key="d5">Providing qualified personnel for watchstanding involves staffing levels and performance methodology evaluated in Factor 3 - Technical Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e150" source="Service Contract Labor Standards" target="Management Approach"><data key="d3">EVALUATED_BY</data><data key="d4">0.5</data><data key="d5">Labor standards for service employees under collective bargaining relate to workforce management aspects in Factor 2 - Management Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e151" source="Collective Bargaining Agreements" target="Management Approach"><data key="d3">EVALUATED_BY</data><data key="d4">0.5</data><data key="d5">Incorporation of collective bargaining agreements impacts workforce organization and supervision evaluated in Factor 2 - Management Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e152" source="Base Operations Support Services" target="Small Business Subcontracting Plan"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.5</data><data key="d5">The Small Business Subcontracting Plan is a standard requirement for government contracts like this SOW to ensure compliance with small business participation goals under FAR 52.219-9. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e153" source="Base Operations Support Services" target="Trash Liners"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.6</data><data key="d5">Trash liners 