nite quantity services are available for purchase under the Base Operations Support Services contract via Fedmall, supporting SOW requirements. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e193" source="Base Operations Support Services" target="Fuel Storage Tank and Berm Inventory"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.85</data><data key="d5">The fuel storage tank and berm inventory supports facility maintenance and operations tasks defined in the Base Operations Support Services SOW for MCSF-BI. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e194" source="Base Operations Support Services" target="Blount Island Shoreline Cleanup Plan"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.85</data><data key="d5">The Blount Island shoreline cleanup plan is a specific environmental deliverable under the base operations support projects in the SOW. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e195" source="Base Operations Support Services" target="Historical Critical Spare Parts Inventory"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.85</data><data key="d5">Historical inventory of critical spare parts for electrical systems aids in facility maintenance deliverables required by the SOW. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e196" source="Base Operations Support Services" target="Transportation Inventories"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.85</data><data key="d5">Transportation inventories for items 02-03-04 support logistics and fleet operations as part of the Base Operations Support Services SOW. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e197" source="Base Operations Support Services" target="Historical Fleet Maintenance Data"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.85</data><data key="d5">Historical fleet maintenance data for NTVE informs the performance of transportation and vehicle support tasks in the SOW. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e198" source="Transportation" target="Mayport BOS"><data key="d3">CHILD_OF</data><data key="d4">0.95</data><data key="d5">Explicitly described as a required service under Base Operations Support, which is the focus of Mayport BOS. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e199" source="Environmental" target="Mayport BOS"><data key="d3">CHILD_OF</data><data key="d4">0.95</data><data key="d5">Explicitly described as environmental services required under Base Operations Support, aligning with Mayport BOS. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e200" source="Transportation Equipment" target="Transportation"><data key="d3">CHILD_OF</data><data key="d4">0.85</data><data key="d5">Focuses on maintenance and repair of equipment specific to the transportation service, showing direct semantic overlap. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e201" source="Transition Period" target="Contract Term"><data key="d3">CHILD_OF</data><data key="d4">0.8</data><data key="d5">Transition periods for mobilization and demobilization are directly tied to the start and end of the contract term. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e202" source="Delivery Period" target="Contract Term"><data key="d3">CHILD_OF</data><data key="d4">0.75</data><data key="d5">Delivery periods for line items correspond to the annual periods outlined in the contract term. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e203" source="Minimum Guarantee" target="Contract Term"><data key="d3">CHILD_OF</data><data key="d4">0.6</data><data key="d5">Applies specifically to the base period of the contract term, with no minimums for option periods. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e204" source="Maximum NTE" target="Contract Term"><data key="d3">CHILD_OF</data><data key="d4">0.6</data><data key="d5">Not-to-exceed values apply to ordering periods and the overall contract term structure. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e205" source="Collective Bargaining Agreements" target="Service Contract Labor Standards"><data key="d3">CHILD_OF</data><data key="d4">0.8</data><data key="d5">Service Contract Labor Standards explicitly reference application to employees under collective bargaining agreements via section 4(c). (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e206" source="Construction Wage Rate Requirements" target="Service Contract Labor Standards"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.5</data><data key="d5">Both involve wage determinations and labor standards, with construction wages incorporated similarly to service contract requirements. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e207" source="Small Business Participation" target="Small Business Size Standard"><data key="d3">REFERENCES</data><data key="d4">0.8</data><data key="d5">Participation requirements for small businesses, including specific categories, are defined and enabled by the acquisition's size standard. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e208" source="Historical And Archaeological Resources" target="Environmental"><data key="d3">CHILD_OF</data><data key="d4">0.6</data><data key="d5">Protection and reporting of historical resources align with environmental services and compliance in base operations support. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e209" source="PM Requirements" target="OEM Specifications"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.7</data><data key="d5">Preventive maintenance tasks are performed in accordance with OEM specifications to ensure system functionality. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e210" source="IMP Requirements" target="OEM Specifications"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.7</data><data key="d5">Inspection, maintenance, and preservation tasks follow OEM guidelines as part of performance methodology. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e211" source="PM Requirements" target="IMP Requirements"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.9</data><data key="d5">Both refer to maintenance tasks for systems in sub-annexes under the same performance methodology. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e212" source="Scheduling" target="Workforce Management"><data key="d3">CHILD_OF</data><data key="d4">0.6</data><data key="d5">Scheduling methodologies for work and contingencies are part of overall workforce management planning. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e213" source="Inspection And Acceptance Location" target="Delivery Period"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.8</data><data key="d5">Both specify the same DoDAAC N46134 and place of performance at Navfac Southeast Pwd Mayport for delivery and acceptance. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e214" source="Consequences Of Contractor's Failure To Perform Required Services" target="Quality Control Program"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.6</data><data key="d5">Nonperformance consequences, including damages, relate to failures in maintaining the quality control program. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e215" source="Miller Act" target="Construction Wage Rate Requirements"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.5</data><data key="d5">Both apply to construction-related aspects, with Miller Act requiring bonds for task orders involving wage requirements. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e216" source="Efficient Labor Approach" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.7</data><data key="d5">Efficient Labor Approach applies best industry practices to meet requirements, supporting Technical Approach through best practices pattern. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e217" source="Reliability-Centered Maintenance Program" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.8</data><data key="d5">Reliability-Centered Maintenance Program is a state-of-the-art methodology for inspection, testing, and repair, demonstrating technical capabilities that support Technical Approach evaluation. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e218" source="Phase-In Plan" target="Factor 2"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.8</data><data key="d5">Phase-In Plan is explicitly included in Factor 2 evaluation of Management Approach, providing logistical and personnel strategies that support management strategies. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e219" source="Small Business Subcontracting Plan" target="Factor 4 Small Business Utilization and Participation"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.95</data><data key="d5">Small Business Subcontracting Plan aligns with small business goals and is incorporated into the contract, directly supporting evaluation under Factor 4 for utilization and participation commitments. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e220" source="L.14 Small Business Subcontracting Plan" target="Factor 4 - Small Business Utilization"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.85</data><data key="d5">L.14 requires submission of SBSP for small business participation, supporting the evaluation criteria in Factor 4 through standard RFP structure and content similarity. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e221" source="Port Operations" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.9</data><data key="d5">Port Operations is a technical annex requiring similarity to RFP requirements, aligning with the Technical Approach evaluation factor for methodology in performance objectives. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e222" source="Facility Investment" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.85</data><data key="d5">Facility Investment includes BOS services like HVAC and fire protection, directly supporting technical methodology descriptions required in the Technical Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e223" source="Electrical" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.9</data><data key="d5">Electrical covers operations, maintenance, and repairs similar to RFP needs, matching the domain alignment pattern for Technical Approach evaluation. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e224" source="Water" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.85</data><data key="d5">Water is a technical area for BOS services, involving water supply and treatment, which addresses performance objectives in the Technical Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e225" source="BSVE" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.8</data><data key="d5">BSVE involves operations and maintenance of equipment, aligning with technical content patterns for evaluating methodology in the Technical Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e226" source="Management and Administration" target="Management Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.75</data><data key="d5">Management and Administration annex, though not technical, relates to administration structure and interfaces, supporting the Management Approach factor. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e227" source="Water Annex" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.85</data><data key="d5">Water Annex specifies recurring BOS services related to water, aligning with technical content for Technical Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e228" source="Attachment JL-8" target="Factor 4 Small Business Utilization and Participation"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.7</data><data key="d5">Attachment JL-8 serves as a template for Small Business Subcontracting Plan, directly relating to small business participation evaluation. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e229" source="Annex 6 Port Operations" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.9</data><data key="d5">Annex 6 Port Operations addresses performance methodology, matching technical content pattern for Technical Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e230" source="Annex 15 Facilities Support" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.95</data><data key="d5">Annex 15 Facilities Support addresses performance methodology, explicitly matching support documentation example. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e231" source="Annex 16 Utilities" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.95</data><data key="d5">Annex 16 Utilities addresses performance methodology, directly from example for technical infrastructure. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e232" source="Annex 17 Transportation" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.95</data><data key="d5">Annex 17 Transportation addresses performance methodology, matching fleet management example. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e233" source="Annex 18 Environmental" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.9</data><data key="d5">Annex 18 Environmental addresses environmental requirements, aligning with compliance example for Technical Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e234" source="Annex 1700000" target="Technical Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.85</data><data key="d5">Annex 1700000 addresses transportation requirements including maintenance, relating to technical methodology in Technical Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge><edge id="e235" source="General Information" target="Management Approach"><data key="d3">RELATED_TO</data><data key="d4">0.6</data><data key="d5">General Information annex, not technical, provides context for administration and management structures evaluated in Management Approach. (LLM-inferred)</data><data key="d6">phase6.1_llm_inference</data></edge></ns0:graph></ns0:graphml>